SENATE BILL 1871
By Johnson
HOUSE BILL 1634
By Lamberth
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 4,
Chapter 3, Part 11 and Title 38, Chapter 8, Part 2,
relative to law enforcement training academies.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 4-3-1106, is amended by
redesignating subsections (a) and (b) as subdivisions (a)(1) and (a)(2) and by adding the
following new subsection (b):
(b) The commissioner of general services may commission the director of a
training academy that falls under the commissioner's general supervision as a law
enforcement officer. The commissioner may commission any staff member of a training
academy that falls under the commissioner's general supervision as a law enforcement
officer upon receiving a written recommendation for the staff member from the director.
A person who is commissioned pursuant to this subsection (b) must comply with § 8-8-
101 and be sworn in pursuant to § 8-18-111.
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 4, Chapter 3, Part 11, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
4-3-1108.
(a) The department of general services may operate a sales facility at a law
enforcement training academy that is under the general supervision of the commissioner
of general services.
(b) The department may assess and collect reasonable fees for services,
programs, lodging, food, facility usage, instructional materials, equipment, and other
functions provided in connection with the operation of a law enforcement training
